# graphify: keep the graph about application/library CODE only.
# git-style patterns, honored by BOTH `graphify extract` and the pre-commit `graphify update`.
# `--code-only` on extract is NOT enough on its own: `update` rejects that flag and re-adds
# these on the next commit, so this ignore file is the update-safe lever.
#
# setup-graphify adapts this to the repo it runs in — uncomment/add the agent, tooling, and
# skill/rule dirs that actually exist here. Delete a line to let that content back into the graph.

# docs, plans, ADRs, instruction files (CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md), skill/rule prose
*.md

# agent / editor / CI config — not application code
.claude/
.codex/
.cursor/
.husky/
.github/
.agents/

# repo tooling and agent-facing skill/rule definitions (adapt paths to this repo)
scripts/
rules/
# e.g. packages/<skills-package>/
